(grunting)

80
00:05:12,342 --> 00:05:28,925
♪

81
00:05:28,925 --> 00:05:30,494
Can you feel it?

82
00:05:30,494 --> 00:05:33,096
That overwhelming
sense of weakness?

83
00:05:33,096 --> 00:05:34,097
In this world...

84
00:05:34,097 --> 00:05:37,200
♪

85
00:05:37,200 --> 00:05:39,970
...it's the winners
that get to make the rules.

86
00:05:39,970 --> 00:05:45,642
♪

87
00:05:45,642 --> 00:05:47,577
(screaming)

88
00:05:52,049 --> 00:05:53,316
(chuckles)

89
00:05:53,316 --> 00:05:55,318
Take a look around you
because we've come to

90
00:05:55,318 --> 00:05:57,621
the moment Psyqualia
showed me before our match

91
00:05:57,621 --> 00:05:59,356
even began.

92
00:05:59,356 --> 00:06:02,826
(chuckles)

93
00:06:02,826 --> 00:06:04,761
(gasping)

94
00:06:08,465 --> 00:06:11,001
Aichi.

95
00:06:11,001 --> 00:06:13,804
(grunting)

96
00:06:13,804 --> 00:06:17,140
It ends like this.

97
00:06:17,140 --> 00:06:18,842
You know it, Aichi.

98
00:06:18,842 --> 00:06:21,845
This isn't what you
pictured for our battle.

99
00:06:21,845 --> 00:06:23,847
(gasps)

100
00:06:23,847 --> 00:06:26,783
It's not over.

101
00:06:26,783 --> 00:06:28,018
(chuckles)

102
00:06:28,018 --> 00:06:30,487
♪

103
00:06:30,487 --> 00:06:33,156
Checking the damage trigger.

104
00:06:33,156 --> 00:06:39,029
♪

105
00:06:39,029 --> 00:06:40,030
He's done for!

106
00:06:40,030 --> 00:06:41,565
I don't think I can watch!

107
00:06:41,565 --> 00:06:42,833
There's still hope.

108
00:06:42,833 --> 00:06:48,171
♪

109
00:06:48,171 --> 00:06:49,239
(gasps)

110
00:06:49,239 --> 00:06:50,841
What?

111
00:06:50,841 --> 00:06:52,709
(grunts)

112
00:06:52,709 --> 00:06:54,111
Heal trigger!

113
00:06:54,111 --> 00:06:58,115
5,000 power to my Vanguard
and then I recover one damage.

114
00:06:58,115 --> 00:07:00,884
♪

115
00:07:00,884 --> 00:07:03,086
Great, your turn.

116
00:07:03,086 --> 00:07:05,088
(cheering)

117
00:07:05,088 --> 00:07:07,224
♪

118
00:07:07,224 --> 00:07:09,559
My word, he failed
to defend against the attack,

119
00:07:09,559 --> 00:07:12,763
but a miracle trigger has
come to Aichi Sendou's rescue!

120
00:07:12,763 --> 00:07:17,033
Don't forget, this
game's not over yet!

121
00:07:17,033 --> 00:07:19,369
These guys are showing us
the best card fight of

122
00:07:19,369 --> 00:07:22,038
their entire lives!

123
00:07:22,038 --> 00:07:23,440
(sighing)

124
00:07:23,440 --> 00:07:29,179
♪

125
00:07:29,179 --> 00:07:32,449
It's my last chance to beat him.

126
00:07:32,449 --> 00:07:36,753
Only, which side of me
should take control?

127
00:07:36,753 --> 00:07:46,096
♪

128
00:07:46,096 --> 00:07:49,466
The shadow
that hungers for control.

129
00:07:49,466 --> 00:07:52,736
Don't get lost; the light
will help us find the way.

130
00:07:52,736 --> 00:07:56,907
♪

131
00:07:56,907 --> 00:07:58,308
What is this?

132
00:07:58,308 --> 00:08:18,895
♪

133
00:08:18,895 --> 00:08:21,598
Amazing.

134
00:08:21,598 --> 00:08:24,835
I get it; my struggle is over!

135
00:08:27,938 --> 00:08:30,574
Avatar of Light and Shadow:

136
00:08:30,574 --> 00:08:33,543
A new strength
borne out of compromise!

137
00:08:33,543 --> 00:08:38,014
Ride, Majesty Lord Blaster!

138
00:08:39,850 --> 00:08:43,787
♪

139
00:08:43,787 --> 00:08:45,288
Huh?

140
00:08:45,288 --> 00:08:50,393
♪

141
00:08:50,393 --> 00:08:51,761
Amazing.

142
00:08:51,761 --> 00:08:55,832
♪

143
00:08:55,832 --> 00:08:59,236
Blaster Dark,
crush that Fatalita!

144
00:08:59,236 --> 00:09:02,038
♪

145
00:09:02,038 --> 00:09:03,306
(grunts)

146
00:09:03,306 --> 00:09:06,409
♪

147
00:09:06,409 --> 00:09:09,512
Boosted by Wingal Brave,
Blaster Blade attacks

148
00:09:09,512 --> 00:09:12,749
Phantom Blaster Overlord!

149
00:09:12,749 --> 00:09:14,184
I don't guard.

150
00:09:14,184 --> 00:09:16,319
♪

151
00:09:16,319 --> 00:09:17,654
(grunting)

152
00:09:17,654 --> 00:09:21,892
♪

153
00:09:21,892 --> 00:09:23,593
Impossible.

154
00:09:23,593 --> 00:09:25,762
How are you doing it;
beating me with that

155
00:09:25,762 --> 00:09:27,631
silly hybrid deck?

156
00:09:27,631 --> 00:09:30,667
Because this deck is part of me.

157
00:09:30,667 --> 00:09:33,336
They're both my avatars
in their own way,

158
00:09:33,336 --> 00:09:35,872
combining my best and worst:

159
00:09:35,872 --> 00:09:38,341
the part of me
that searched for a new power

160
00:09:38,341 --> 00:09:40,944
and the part that
found inner purpose.

161
00:09:40,944 --> 00:09:43,813
The path I walked
led me to myself!

162
00:09:43,813 --> 00:09:45,515
(grunts)

163
00:09:45,515 --> 00:09:49,452
Supported by Marron,
Majesty Lord Blaster attacks!

164
00:09:49,452 --> 00:09:51,821
♪

165
00:09:51,821 --> 00:09:54,491
Activating my Vanguard's
ultimate skill.

166
00:09:54,491 --> 00:09:58,261
Blaster Blade and Blaster Dark
are moved into the soul.

167
00:09:58,261 --> 00:10:00,030
(grunting)

168
00:10:00,030 --> 00:10:06,069
♪

169
00:10:06,069 --> 00:10:10,807
Aichi Sendou, it's time
for you to make a choice.

170
00:10:10,807 --> 00:10:12,776
I choose...

171
00:10:12,776 --> 00:10:22,519
♪

172
00:10:22,519 --> 00:10:23,520
Huh?

173
00:10:23,520 --> 00:10:29,392
♪

174
00:10:29,392 --> 00:10:32,162
That card is
the perfect fit for you.

175
00:10:32,162 --> 00:10:36,466
♪

176
00:10:36,466 --> 00:10:39,235
I've never seen
anything like this before.

177
00:10:39,235 --> 00:10:44,541
♪

178
00:10:47,978 --> 00:11:01,257
♪

179
00:11:01,257 --> 00:11:05,662
With this ability,
my Vanguard gains 10,000 power!

180
00:11:05,662 --> 00:11:08,465
♪

181
00:11:08,465 --> 00:11:11,768
As if that weren't enough,
he also has a passive skill!

182
00:11:11,768 --> 00:11:13,636
Since Blaster Blade
and Blaster Dark

183
00:11:13,636 --> 00:11:16,206
are in the soul,
Majesty Lord Blaster

184
00:11:16,206 --> 00:11:19,309
gains 2,000 power
and +1 critical

185
00:11:19,309 --> 00:11:20,677
at all times!

186
00:11:20,677 --> 00:11:22,078
Impossible!

187
00:11:22,078 --> 00:11:24,214
How is it that you're able
to make two enemy clans

188
00:11:24,214 --> 00:11:26,182
work so well together?

189
00:11:26,182 --> 00:11:28,918
How can you benefit
from both sides?

190
00:11:28,918 --> 00:11:33,089
Because Majesty Lord Blaster
opened my eyes to the truth.

191
00:11:33,089 --> 00:11:36,226
Thanks to this card,
I understand what I've become.

192
00:11:36,226 --> 00:11:39,996
In the past, I got scared,
I didn't understand my power,

193
00:11:39,996 --> 00:11:42,198
but now, I'm the one in control.

194
00:11:42,198 --> 00:11:43,199
(grunts)

195
00:11:43,199 --> 00:11:47,971
♪

196
00:11:47,971 --> 00:11:50,440
Using Psyqualia turned me
into a different person

197
00:11:50,440 --> 00:11:52,842
and I ended up
hurting those I loved!

198
00:11:52,842 --> 00:11:55,045
I won't make excuses
for my actions or

199
00:11:55,045 --> 00:11:56,312
the things I said.

200
00:11:56,312 --> 00:11:59,249
I jumped at the chance
to finally feel strong.

201
00:11:59,249 --> 00:12:03,053
Bring given so much strength,
it was overwhelming,

202
00:12:03,053 --> 00:12:06,056
but that was only a part of me.

203
00:12:06,056 --> 00:12:08,291
I've accepted who I am
and it's time for you

204
00:12:08,291 --> 00:12:09,292
to do the same.

205
00:12:09,292 --> 00:12:10,427
What?

206
00:12:10,427 --> 00:12:12,162
You were searching
for a way to get better,

207
00:12:12,162 --> 00:12:16,332
and I think you lost
yourself in the process.

208
00:12:16,332 --> 00:12:19,602
Think about why
you wanted that power.

209
00:12:19,602 --> 00:12:22,105
Can you even remember anymore?

210
00:12:22,105 --> 00:12:25,375
So you could win nationals
with your friends beside you.

211
00:12:25,375 --> 00:12:29,512
♪

212
00:12:29,512 --> 00:12:32,649
(all chuckling)

213
00:12:32,649 --> 00:12:34,017
Stop it!

214
00:12:34,017 --> 00:12:36,086
(grunting)

215
00:12:36,086 --> 00:12:37,153
No!

216
00:12:37,153 --> 00:12:39,089
Silence, you little fool!

217
00:12:39,089 --> 00:12:40,590
I guard!

218
00:12:44,961 --> 00:12:46,763
Spare me your pity.

219
00:12:46,763 --> 00:12:52,335
You don't know me,
or what I'm capable of doing.

220
00:12:52,335 --> 00:12:53,837
Ren.

221
00:12:57,073 --> 00:12:58,975
Checking the Twin Drive.

222
00:13:01,377 --> 00:13:02,879
Second check.

223
00:13:04,314 --> 00:13:07,617
Now, for my winning image.

224
00:13:07,617 --> 00:13:09,252
Just picture it,
try to remember

225
00:13:09,252 --> 00:13:10,954
what it felt like
to count on your friends

226
00:13:10,954 --> 00:13:15,158
to help you when
you needed it most.

227
00:13:15,158 --> 00:13:17,193
Critical trigger!

228
00:13:17,193 --> 00:13:20,563
Giving both of the effects
to Majesty Lord Blaster!

229
00:13:20,563 --> 00:13:30,807
♪

230
00:13:30,807 --> 00:13:32,742
What is this that I'm feeling?

231
00:13:32,742 --> 00:13:40,750
♪

232
00:13:40,750 --> 00:13:42,785
That was a great match.

233
00:13:42,785 --> 00:13:43,920
You're getting better.

234
00:13:43,920 --> 00:13:45,922
Next, you've gotta face me.

235
00:13:45,922 --> 00:13:47,423
No prob.

236
00:13:47,423 --> 00:13:49,159
(chuckling)

237
00:13:49,159 --> 00:13:50,994
My friends.

238
00:13:50,994 --> 00:13:53,229
(grunts)

239
00:13:53,229 --> 00:14:18,888
♪

240
00:14:18,888 --> 00:14:24,294
Ren, I knew that the real you
was hiding somewhere in there.

241
00:14:24,294 --> 00:14:25,695
(grunts)

242
00:14:25,695 --> 00:14:34,571
♪

243
00:14:34,571 --> 00:14:35,838
(grunts)

244
00:14:35,838 --> 00:14:40,977
♪

245
00:14:40,977 --> 00:14:42,579
(screams)

246
00:14:42,579 --> 00:14:46,983
♪

247
00:14:46,983 --> 00:14:49,285
You're fine.

248
00:14:49,285 --> 00:14:50,687
Aichi.

249
00:14:50,687 --> 00:14:52,355
(grunts)

250
00:14:52,355 --> 00:15:01,364
♪

251
00:15:01,364 --> 00:15:03,900
You're safe, Ren.

252
00:15:03,900 --> 00:15:35,331
♪

253
00:15:35,331 --> 00:15:37,867
That's it...I lost.

254
00:15:37,867 --> 00:15:55,118
♪

255
00:15:55,118 --> 00:15:57,220
The winner is Aichi Sendou!

256
00:15:57,220 --> 00:15:59,155
(cheering)

257
00:16:05,728 --> 00:16:09,632
Our Vanguards have reached
the decision my people needed.

258
00:16:09,632 --> 00:16:26,482
♪

259
00:16:26,482 --> 00:16:28,718
(grunting, struggling)

260
00:16:28,718 --> 00:16:42,165
♪

261
00:16:42,165 --> 00:16:44,967
We're defeated.

262
00:16:44,967 --> 00:16:47,804
The time for fighting
has come to an end.

263
00:16:47,804 --> 00:16:49,672
The other clans
are waiting for us.

264
00:16:49,672 --> 00:16:57,380
♪

265
00:16:57,380 --> 00:17:00,116
The royal paladins
are victorious.

266
00:17:00,116 --> 00:17:02,618
Too cool, it's amazing
that the forces clashing

267
00:17:02,618 --> 00:17:03,986
here on Cray were synchronized

268
00:17:03,986 --> 00:17:05,988
with our card fighters
back on Earth.

269
00:17:05,988 --> 00:17:08,024
It would appear the result
of the matchup wasn't

270
00:17:08,024 --> 00:17:10,693
the only thing
that became synchronized.

271
00:17:10,693 --> 00:17:12,462
I've never seen
those two treat each other

272
00:17:12,462 --> 00:17:14,263
with such understanding.

273
00:17:14,263 --> 00:17:16,165
I believe they've learned
from their connection

274
00:17:16,165 --> 00:17:19,402
with Ren and Aichi.

275
00:17:19,402 --> 00:17:22,739
None of this would have been
possible without your help.

276
00:17:22,739 --> 00:17:26,175
On behalf of
the planet Cray, thank you.

277
00:17:26,175 --> 00:17:29,345
Until next time.

278
00:17:29,345 --> 00:17:30,880
Huh?

279
00:17:30,880 --> 00:17:32,148
Uh‐oh.

280
00:17:32,148 --> 00:17:34,550
Sorry, I totally blanked out.

281
00:17:34,550 --> 00:17:35,585
Rekka?

282
00:17:35,585 --> 00:17:37,653
What?

283
00:17:37,653 --> 00:17:39,756
Bro, bro!

284
00:17:39,756 --> 00:17:41,524
Aichi, you did it!

285
00:17:41,524 --> 00:17:43,793
Wow, this means that we're...

286
00:17:43,793 --> 00:17:47,296
we just won
the national championship!

287
00:17:47,296 --> 00:17:48,798
I can't‐‐

288
00:17:48,798 --> 00:17:50,366
(sobbing)

289
00:17:50,366 --> 00:17:52,969
It's okay, Kamui.

290
00:17:52,969 --> 00:17:55,037
That was
an incredible card fight.

291
00:17:55,037 --> 00:17:56,639
Epic battle, yo.

292
00:17:56,639 --> 00:17:57,907
That was awesome.

293
00:17:57,907 --> 00:18:00,109
I knew he could do it.

294
00:18:00,109 --> 00:18:02,979
Looks like my number one pupil's
been doing his homework.

295
00:18:02,979 --> 00:18:04,480
(giggling)

296
00:18:04,480 --> 00:18:06,149
I'm so proud of those guys.

297
00:18:06,149 --> 00:18:10,186
♪

298
00:18:10,186 --> 00:18:13,189
So, what now?

299
00:18:13,189 --> 00:18:17,126
I dunno, I think I'd just
like to go someplace else.

300
00:18:17,126 --> 00:18:19,328
And it's probably time
we changed the team policy

301
00:18:19,328 --> 00:18:20,530
on losing games.

302
00:18:20,530 --> 00:18:21,864
(gasps)

303
00:18:21,864 --> 00:18:25,368
Don't you think, Asaka?

304
00:18:25,368 --> 00:18:26,536
Really?

305
00:18:26,536 --> 00:18:35,578
♪

306
00:18:35,578 --> 00:18:37,847
Next time, Kai,
I'm gonna beat you

307
00:18:37,847 --> 00:18:42,218
with my own strength
the way I always wanted to.

308
00:18:42,218 --> 00:18:43,286
Ren.

309
00:18:43,286 --> 00:18:49,292
♪

310
00:18:49,292 --> 00:18:50,793
Well.

311
00:18:50,793 --> 00:18:59,469
♪

312
00:18:59,469 --> 00:19:03,506
He's back; Thank you, Aichi.

313
00:19:03,506 --> 00:19:09,045
♪

314
00:19:09,045 --> 00:19:11,781
There are tears of joy
being shed down on

315
00:19:11,781 --> 00:19:13,816
the stadium floor this day!

316
00:19:13,816 --> 00:19:15,918
Team Q4 has come
from behind to win

317
00:19:15,918 --> 00:19:18,154
their first
national championship.

318
00:19:18,154 --> 00:19:21,157
Looks like our work
here is finally over.

319
00:19:21,157 --> 00:19:23,593
What's next for the three of us?

320
00:19:23,593 --> 00:19:27,363
There may come a time
when we're needed again.

321
00:19:27,363 --> 00:19:29,599
But I think we deserve
to take a break and get

322
00:19:29,599 --> 00:19:30,867
out of the public eye.

323
00:19:30,867 --> 00:19:35,271
♪

324
00:19:35,271 --> 00:19:37,139
Please join me in
a thundering round

325
00:19:37,139 --> 00:19:41,210
of applause for
our top team: Q4!

326
00:19:41,210 --> 00:19:43,279
(cheering)

327
00:19:43,279 --> 00:19:55,591
♪

328
00:19:55,591 --> 00:19:56,993
Ah!

329
00:19:56,993 --> 00:19:59,195
♪

330
00:19:59,195 --> 00:20:01,731
Thank you.

331
00:20:01,731 --> 00:20:03,132
Huh?

332
00:20:03,132 --> 00:20:12,475
♪

333
00:20:16,779 --> 00:20:18,014
Good morning.

334
00:20:18,014 --> 00:20:19,348
That's not what
you said five minutes ago

335
00:20:19,348 --> 00:20:22,184
when I woke you up.

336
00:20:22,184 --> 00:20:24,787
Breakfast time.

337
00:20:24,787 --> 00:20:25,788
Here.

338
00:20:25,788 --> 00:20:28,157
Oh, thanks, Emi.

339
00:20:28,157 --> 00:20:30,026
And I thought winning
the national tournament

340
00:20:30,026 --> 00:20:31,961
would transform you
into someone a little easier

341
00:20:31,961 --> 00:20:32,995
to live with.

342
00:20:32,995 --> 00:20:34,764
Oh, don't be silly.

343
00:20:34,764 --> 00:20:38,668
He's still your brother
even if he is a champion.

344
00:20:38,668 --> 00:20:41,737
Yeah, after nationals,
things seemed to go back

345
00:20:41,737 --> 00:20:44,907
to the way they'd always been.

346
00:20:44,907 --> 00:20:46,709
See ya later!

347
00:20:46,709 --> 00:20:49,011
With one major difference:

348
00:20:49,011 --> 00:20:51,547
My Psyqualia,
that mysterious power,

349
00:20:51,547 --> 00:20:54,116
has disappeared.

350
00:20:54,116 --> 00:20:56,986
I haven't felt it once
since the tournament ended.

351
00:20:58,721 --> 00:21:01,791
I'm still not sure exactly why.

352
00:21:01,791 --> 00:21:05,061
Whatever, I'm happy it's gone.

353
00:21:05,061 --> 00:21:08,497
I realize now that I
can be strong on my own,

354
00:21:08,497 --> 00:21:10,933
and besides, Psyqualia
made me lose sight

355
00:21:10,933 --> 00:21:14,870
of what actually mattered,
the reason I started playing.

356
00:21:16,672 --> 00:21:18,841
Huh?

357
00:21:18,841 --> 00:21:20,076
(all chuckling)

358
00:21:20,076 --> 00:21:21,277
Hey, guys.

359
00:21:21,277 --> 00:21:23,279
♪

360
00:21:23,279 --> 00:21:26,182
(chuckling)

361
00:21:26,182 --> 00:21:28,551
You took your time.

362
00:21:28,551 --> 00:21:29,919
Sorry.

363
00:21:29,919 --> 00:21:31,320
Kai's been waiting around
to have a game with you

364
00:21:31,320 --> 00:21:33,456
all morning.

365
00:21:33,456 --> 00:21:35,257
A proper game this time.

366
00:21:35,257 --> 00:21:38,227
♪

367
00:21:38,227 --> 00:21:40,863
Why'd you wait around
to battle with me?

368
00:21:40,863 --> 00:21:42,098
'Cause you're one
of the strongest

369
00:21:42,098 --> 00:21:44,066
card fighters I know.

370
00:21:44,066 --> 00:21:45,935
Really?

371
00:21:45,935 --> 00:21:48,471
Well, this match has been
a long time in the making.

372
00:21:48,471 --> 00:21:51,741
I can't wait for Aichi
to beat that jerk.

373
00:21:51,741 --> 00:21:54,977
No, on second thought,
Kai is a pretty cool dude.

374
00:21:54,977 --> 00:21:55,978
You know what?

375
00:21:55,978 --> 00:21:57,947
I really envy them.

376
00:21:57,947 --> 00:22:00,816
There are probably thousands
of card fights going on all over

377
00:22:00,816 --> 00:22:03,786
the planet right now,
but I seriously doubt

378
00:22:03,786 --> 00:22:06,055
you could find anyone
that enjoys Vanguard

379
00:22:06,055 --> 00:22:08,424
more than those two guys.

380
00:22:08,424 --> 00:22:10,226
They're pretty lucky.

381
00:22:10,226 --> 00:22:12,395
You ready, Aichi?

382
00:22:12,395 --> 00:22:14,630
Mm!

383
00:22:14,630 --> 00:22:17,400
‐Stand up, the Vanguard!
‐Stand up, the Vanguard!

384
00:22:17,400 --> 00:22:24,006
♪

385
00:22:26,876 --> 00:23:56,532
♪

